==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[mīl]]''

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪl|-aɪl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A unit of measure (length or distance) equal to 5,280 [[feet]] (8 [[furlong]]s) in the Customary/[[Imperial]] system of measurements. One mile is equal to 1.609344 [[kilometer]]s.
# A Roman unit of measure equal to about 1620 yards or 1481m.
# A track race of one mile in length; sometimes used to refer to the 1500m race.
#:''The runners competed in the '''mile'''.''
#  {{slang}} A great distance.
#:''The shot missed by a '''mile'''.''

